decks.notes: The key strategy of this deck is to control the game through a combination of countering spells, card draw, and disruption, while setting up a win condition through milling the opponent with cards like Dream's Grip, Brain Freeze, and Into the Flood Maw. Lier, Disciple of the Drowned provides recursion for important spells and enables flexibility in the deck's game plan. By utilizing a high number of instant spells and cantrips, the deck aims to generate card advantage and maintain tempo advantage over the opponent. The inclusion of cards like Pact of Negation and Force of Will ensures protection against key threats, while cards like Thought Scour and Intuition help dig for win conditions and answers.

The main strategy of this deck is to control the game through manipulation of resources, disruption of opponent's plans, and strategic reanimation of powerful creatures. With Aminatou, the Fateshifter as the commander, the deck focuses on leveraging her abilities to flicker key creatures, draw cards, and set up advantageous board states. The deck includes a range of removal spells, counterspells, and graveyard recursion to deal with threats and maintain control of the game. By utilizing Aminatou's abilities in combination with powerful creatures like Agent of Treachery and Archon of Cruelty, the deck aims to outvalue and outmaneuver the opponent, ultimately securing victory through superior card advantage and board presence.

This deck focuses on aggressive plays with a combination of small but powerful creatures and disruptive spells to control the board. The commanders, Rograkh and Silas Renn, provide a fast and efficient way to deal damage while also providing card advantage. The deck includes a variety of removal spells, counterspells, and card draw to maintain tempo and keep the opponent on the back foot. The aim is to pressure the opponent early and close out the game quickly before they can establish their own game plan. With a mix of evasive threats and versatile spells, this deck is designed to be proactive and adaptable in order to maintain dominance in the 1 vs 1 format.

The deck revolves around utilizing Sheoldred, the Apocalypse's ability to reanimate creatures from both your own graveyard and your opponent's graveyard while controlling the board with various removal spells and disruption. The goal is to overwhelm your opponent with a constant stream of threats and disruption, taking advantage of the powerful recursion engine provided by the commander. The deck also includes a strong suite of tutors and card draw spells to quickly find the necessary pieces to execute your game plan. In addition, the deck features a mana denial strategy with cards like Cabal Coffers and Urborg, Tomb of Yawgmoth to further disrupt your opponent's game plan and secure victory.
